######################################################################
## 52North SOS Uncertainty Enabled Sensor Observation Service
######################################################################

This project contains the uncertainty extension for the 52°North Sensor 
Observation Service.

This project is still under construction.


######################################################################
## Folder structure:

The project contains the following folders:
52n-sos-uncertainty:	extensions to different SOS packages
conf:					customized build properties
db:						SQL scripts to extend the data model and insert
						sample data
examples:				SOS requests to register sensors, insert
						observations and get observations

######################################################################
## Project configuration:

Adjust the following properties in your conf\build.properties file and
copy it into your SOS configuration directory (52n-sos\conf).

conf.sos.ds.connectionstring=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/SosDatabase
							connection string to the DB
conf.sos.ds.user=postgres	your DB-username
conf.sos.ds.password=*****	your DB-password


######################################################################
## Installation instructions:

#1 Checkout this project and 52North SOS (https://svn.52north.org/svn/swe/
main/SOS/Service/trunk/SOS/52n-sos , documentation: /doc/how2install_SOS).

#2 Extend your DB's datamodel by executing the following SQL script on
your database:
db/extend_datamodel_postgres83.sql

#3 Configure this project (see above).

#4 Add this project's module to your SOS pom (52n-sos/pom.xml) modules,
e.g. add:

<module>../u-sos/52n-sos-uncertainty</module>

to:

<modules>
	<module>52n-sos-ogc</module>
	<module>52n-sos-core</module>
	<module>52n-sos-coding</module>
	<module>52n-sos-dao-postgis</module>
	<module>52n-sos-service</module>
</modules>

Don't forget to use the correct relative path from SOS project to u-SOS
project. 

#5 Add this project as a dependency to your SOS service module's pom
(52n-sos\52n-sos-service\pom.xml).
Add:

<dependency>
	<groupId>${project.groupId}</groupId>
	<artifactId>52n-sos-uncertainty</artifactId>
	<version>${project.version}</version>
</dependency>

to:

<dependencies></dependencies>
